comments:
Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Frant in Tunbridge 
    Wells Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of 
    Tunbridge Wells. See also Table 2, note (e).

In 1894 the  part in Kent became part of the 
    parish of Tonbridge Rural, so that thereafter Frant was wholly in East Sussex. 
    See also Table 2, notes (c) and (f).

In 1894 the part in East Sussex was transfererd to Kent, so that thereafter Lamberhurst was 
    entirely in Kent. See also Table 
    2, note (e).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed the parish of Broadwater Down. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).
